<subSubSection id="C337088DF778B139B182FBE43727463B" pageId="13" pageNumber="534" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B925B06F778B139B182FBE43727463B" blockId="13.[151,1437,223,1402]" pageId="13" pageNumber="534">
COMMENTS: Date and place agree with the journal entries. In the (Latin) text Sundevall referred to Levaillant’s description as “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D2085F778B139B00CFBBF3073471B" authority="(l'Oliva)" baseAuthorityName="l'Oliva" box="[329,586,1087,1113]" class="Aves" family="Malaconotidae" genus="Malaconotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="534" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="oleagineo">
<emphasis id="B9598714F778B139B00CFBBF3073471B" box="[329,586,1087,1113]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="534">M. oleagineo (l’Oliva)</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” (
<bibRefCitation id="EFBC26F7F778B139B322FBC03126471B" author="Levaillant, F." box="[615,799,1087,1113]" pageId="13" pageNumber="534" refId="ref29075" refString="Levaillant, F. (1799 - 1808) Histoire naturelle des oiseaux d'Afrique, 6 volumes. Chez J. J. Fuchs, Paris, 194 + 206 + 231 + 141 + 163 + 188 pp." type="book" year="1799">Levaillant 1799</bibRefCitation>
; pl. 75, 105–110), and referred to the species in French only (
<emphasis id="B9598714F778B139B199FB9C3312473F" box="[220,299,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="534">l’Oliva</emphasis>
). It was later formally described in 1809 by Shaw as 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D2085F778B139B2DAFB9B3666473F" authorityName="Vieillot" authorityYear="1818" box="[927,1119,1123,1149]" class="Aves" family="Laniidae" genus="Lanius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="534" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="olivaceus">
<emphasis id="B9598714F778B139B2DAFB9B3666473F" box="[927,1119,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="534">Lanius olivaceus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Sundevall must have been well aware of Shaw’s description. It was not intended as a new name for 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D2085F778B139B28CFB7736BF47E3" authorityName="Vieillot" authorityYear="1818" box="[969,1158,1159,1185]" class="Aves" family="Laniidae" genus="Lanius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="534" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="olivaceus">
<emphasis id="B9598714F778B139B28CFB7736BF47E3" box="[969,1158,1159,1185]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="534">Lanius olivaceus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, because Sundevall consequently announced new names with “nob.” (= mine) and is just a Latinisation of the French name and therefore has no nomenclatural status. The first paragraph of Sundevall’s description (
<bibRefCitation id="EFBC26F7F778B139B2AFFB3036EC47A8" author="Sundevall, C. J." box="[1002,1237,1231,1258]" pageId="13" pageNumber="534" pagination="96 - 111" refId="ref29984" refString="Sundevall, C. J. (1850) Foglar fran sodra Afrika. Ofversigt af Kongliga Vetenskaps-akademiens forhandlingar, 7 (4), 96 - 111." type="journal article" year="1850">Sundevall 1850: 106</bibRefCitation>
) is “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D2085F778B139B44FFB303322464F" authorityName="Sundevall and l'Oliva" authorityYear="1850" class="Aves" family="Malaconotidae" genus="Malaconotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="534" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rubiginosus">
<emphasis id="B9598714F778B139B44FFB303322464F" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="534">Malaconotus rubiginosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
nob., l’Oliva jeune, Le Vaill. Afr. 75, 2, it is a truly distinct species, of which the adults and juveniles of both sexes have been collected by Wahlberg in the lower Caffraria, where it is found together with 
<emphasis id="B9598714F778B139B476FAE837B04673" box="[1331,1417,1303,1329]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="534">L’Oliva</emphasis>
”. 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D2085F778B139B1D2FAC430834617" authority="Sundevall and l'Oliva" authorityName="Sundevall and l'Oliva" authorityYear="1850" box="[151,698,1339,1365]" class="Aves" family="Malaconotidae" genus="Malaconotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="534" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rubiginosus">
<emphasis id="B9598714F778B139B1D2FAC433814617" box="[151,440,1339,1365]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="534">Malaconotus rubiginosus</emphasis>
Sundevall and 
<emphasis id="B9598714F778B139B322FAC430834617" box="[615,698,1339,1365]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="534">l’Oliva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B9598714F778B139B387FAC3313B4617" box="[706,770,1340,1365]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="534">jeune</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFBC26F7F778B139B257FAC431E14617" author="Levaillant, F." box="[786,984,1339,1365]" pageId="13" pageNumber="534" refId="ref29075" refString="Levaillant, F. (1799 - 1808) Histoire naturelle des oiseaux d'Afrique, 6 volumes. Chez J. J. Fuchs, Paris, 194 + 206 + 231 + 141 + 163 + 188 pp." type="book" year="1799">Levaillant, 1799</bibRefCitation>
, vol. 2, plate 75, figure 2), are distinct species, showing the adult and young of both sexes, and were confused with 
<emphasis id="B9598714F778B139B55AFAA0364B463B" box="[1055,1138,1375,1401]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="534">l’Oliva</emphasis>
by Levaillant.
</paragraph>
